orig_task: In the domain of Human Anatomy: Is class Serum a subclass of Skin?
task_gold_reason:
"In blood, the serum is the component that is neither a blood cell (serum does not contain white or red blood cells) nor a clotting factor; it is the blood plasma not including the fibrinogens."(http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Serum_%28blood%29)
Therefore Serum is a kind of substance. It is not a kind of Skin.
